# Once included with every Computer, now recovery CDs are often required to be made by home users. If a User does not create their Own CD they can sometimes contact the Computer’s Manufacturer and purchase one for a fee. Some companies still include Recovery CDs with units, including Dell, Toshiba, some Gateways, and Apple. Others, such as HP and Compaq always require you to create your own CD and will charge up to $100 USD for a new set.